abstracts.cdata!:
The project includes the construction
            and improvement of three roads (1,450 km) in the
            country's southeast, central and northeast regions.
            They will extend the existing road network into the eastern
            part of Iran. The Shahpasand-Meshed-Afghan Border road will
            at the same time provide an international road connection
            with land-locked Afghanistan to the east. The project also
            includes the paving of the arterial highway between Teheran
            and the Caspian region (230 km).
